cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.RO 

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques applied to medical imaging data. The paper specifically focuses on detecting and augmenting imperfect bilateral symmetry in CT scans of human anatomy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves 3D imaging and visualization techniques, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves medical applications, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.RO (Robotics).
